HEADWORD: Hyomental
<hw>Hy`o*men"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hyo-</ets>
+ <ets>mental</ets> of the chin.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Between
the hyoid bone and the lower jaw, pertaining to them; suprahyoid;
submaxillary; <as>as, the <ex>hyomental</ex> region of the front of the
neck</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

